{"key":"processedPost-10321392","value":{"id":10321392,"first":10315708,"last":10321392,"when":1242049986,"utime":"05/11/09 04:53 PM","content":"You want a very high CO2 level when colonizing bulk substrates.&nbsp; If not, your mycelium will turn most of the material you want for fruiting later into CO2 now.&nbsp; In other words, you're saving your substrate for the flush rather than have the mycelium munch it all during colonization. However you go about that is fine.&nbsp; If it's in a nearly sealed tub with a small amount of gas exchange, you don't need the plastic cover.<br />RR","title":"Re: Do I have to cover spawned straw with plastic?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}